Text align. property
->text-align:left/start
->text-align:right/end
->text-align:center
->text-align:justify

The alignment will be based on the parent

example:
<html>
    <head>
        </head>
        <body>
            <div class="main">
            <h1>Hello</h1>
            </div>
            </body>
            
</html>
.main{
   
    border: 2px solid black;
    width:300px;
    align-items: center;
    margin-left:200px ;
}
h1{
    text-align: center;
}

--------A1 -------- >   --------------->---------------------------div(main)----------------------
                      |                                                                           |
                      |                                                                           |
                      | -------------A2 >----h1-------- Center                                    |
                      |                                                                           |
                      |                                                                           |
                      ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To get space for div(main) or to place it in center,left or right use "Margin Property"
To get space for h1 or to place it in center,left,right use "Text-align Property"
